### Test Zar3a API

## 1️⃣ Backend Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000
Accept: application/json

###

## 2️⃣ Register New User
POST http://localhost:5000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Ahmed Test",
  "username": "ahmadtest123",
  "email": "ahmadtest@example.com",
  "phone": "1234567890",
  "password": "TestPassword123"
}

### Store userId from response above and use in next request

## 3️⃣ Choose Role (Replace :userId with actual ID from step 2)
POST http://localhost:5000/auth/choose-role/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "FARMER"
}

###

## 4️⃣ Complete Farmer Profile
POST http://localhost:5000/auth/complete/farmer/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "farmSize": "5 hectares",
  "soilType": "clay",
  "location": "Cairo, Egypt"
}

###

## 5️⃣ Login Test
POST http://localhost:5000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ahmadtest@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123"
}

###

## 6️⃣ Get Current User (use accessToken from login response)
GET http://localhost:5000/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: application/json

###
